<p>I am using <code>RegEx</code> to make one of the <code>PathParam</code> as optional in my JAX-RS resource. </p>  <p>My <code>@GET</code> resource is <code>employee\getRecords\id\{id}\group\{group}</code> , Now to make the second param <code>group</code> as optional I am using <code>@Path(value = "/id/{id}/{group:(\\w+)?}"</code> which works as expected.</p>  <p>Now the problem is, I have one more <code>@POST</code> resource <code>employee\getRecords\id\{id}\group\{group}</code>. When I hit the <code>@GET</code> resource with or without second param i.e. <code>group</code> it works fine. But if I hit the <code>@POST</code> request it gives me 405 method not allowed exception.</p>  <p>Please help.! Thanks in advance.</p>  <p>P.S. : If I remove the RegEx from <code>@GET</code> resource <code>[employee\getRecords\id\{id}\group\{group}]</code>, both <code>@GET</code> and <code>@POST</code> works fine.</p>